[Name] LibXCrypt
[Summary] Modern library for one-way hashing of passwords
[Description] LibXCrypt is a modern library for one-way hashing of passwords. It supports a wide variety of both modern and historical hashing methods: yescrypt, gost-yescrypt, sm3-yescrypt, scrypt, bcrypt, sha512crypt, sha256crypt, sm3crypt, md5crypt, SunMD5, sha1crypt, NT, bsdicrypt, bigcrypt, and descrypt. It provides the traditional Unix crypt and crypt_r interfaces, as well as a set of extended interfaces pioneered by Openwall Linux, crypt_rn, crypt_ra, crypt_gensalt, crypt_gensalt_rn, and crypt_gensalt_ra.
[License] LGPL
[Homepage] https://github.com/besser82/libxcrypt/
